      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/8",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"مَا أَخَذَتِ اَلْحِبَالَةُ وَ قَطَعَتْ مِنْهُ فَهُوَ مَيْتَةٌ وَ مَا أَدْرَكْتَ مِنْ سَائِرِ جَسَدِهِ حَيّاً فَذَكِّهِ ثُمَّ كُلْ مِنْهُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4128 - Aban narrated from Abdur-Rahman ibn Abi Abdullah who said:\nAbu Abdullah (as), said: \"Whatever is caught by a snare and has part of it severed, then it is considered dead. However, if you find the rest of its body alive, then perform the proper slaughtering (Zabiha) and eat from it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
